line_1: Whose Fancy dwells upon a wealthy 'Squire:
line_2: Her wounded Ears their hateful Whinings tire,

line_1: Th' ambitious bosom of the landed 'squire,
line_2: But with most warmth her dress and airs inspire

line_1: He weds — a cousin of the 'squire;
There goes my lady, and there goes the 'squire,
line_2: The flame extinct, he views the roving fire,
Of base intent and foul desire,
